<subSubSection id="C3346522FFE9B076FF50FF151BEAE676" pageId="3" pageNumber="319" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9136A9FFE9B076FF50FF151BEAE676" blockId="3.[151,1436,153,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis id="B95AEABBFFE9B076FF50FF151827E792" bold="true" box="[199,334,225,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis id="B95AEABBFFE9B076FCABFF151AF9E792" box="[828,912,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">batillus</emphasis>
(= shovel) with a Latin superlative ending 
<emphasis id="B95AEABBFFE9B076FAF2FF161CFFE792" box="[1381,1430,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">-osa</emphasis>
, referring to the shovel-shaped labial palpus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
